1.ABOUT:
Oz Biometry - Biometric face recognition with the highest accuracy: 99.99% in NIST FRVT. Developed by Oz Forensics specialists, the biometric module incorporates the latest practices in artificial intelligence and is consistently improved by continuous data enrichment. Face recognition algorithm from Oz Forensics achieved one of the best test results in accuracy on LFW dataset in University of Massachusetts tests in 2020 MIT LFW. The Oz Biometry module allows to identify people with a speed .f less than 1 second and with 99.87% accuracy (according to MIT LFW tests).

Oz Forensics Face Recognition algorithms allow:
●	Detect and highlight the best shot from the video;
●	Compare face from photo with face photo from ID;
●	Perform a search in the biometric database.
